"For the first task of my Digital Literacy project, I created a visual infographic using Canva. 
I chose this tool because it offers professional templates that are easy to customize for a student audience. 
My design focuses on four main pillars: understanding digital literacy, practicing internet safety, maintaining professional email etiquette, and mastering essential digital tools like GitHub and Google Workspace.

While making this, I found it very interesting how a few simple tips, like enabling Two-Factor Authentication, can drastically improve our online security. 
The most difficult part was condensing the broad topic of 'Digital Literacy' into just a few sentences that my batchmates could quickly read and understand. 
This task helped me realize that as a Student Digital Ambassador, my communication needs to be both visually appealing and technically accurate.
Learning how to organize information into a 4-part layout was a great way to practice visual communication."
